Sign up here to get Inside the Mets delivered to your inbox each Friday morning. Jeff McNeil’s smooth swings to begin this Mets season have mirrored his offseason on the golf course. Participating in a match play tournament over the winter near his home in Nipomo, Calif., he shot a career-best 63. The Mets second baseman grew up with the game, and was good enough as a junior amateur to consider a professional career. In 2019, Golf Magazine named him the best golfer among MLB players. McNeil this week discussed his game with Post Sports+.